Referred to Committee on Natural Resources
SUMMARY—Revises provisions relating to the operation of
vessels. (BDR 43-371)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: Increases or Newly
Provides for Term of Imprisonment in County or City
Jail or Detention Facility.
Effect on the State: Yes.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to vessels; prohibiting the operation of a vessel in
excess of a certain speed within 600 feet of the shoreline
of Lake Tahoe; revising provisions relating to the
violation of certain provisions of the Code of Ordinances
of the Tahoe Regional Planning Agency; providing a
penalty; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, it is a misdemeanor to operate a vessel or permit a vessel to
2 be operated at a speed in excess of 5 nautical miles per hour within 100 feet of a
3 person who is bathing, wading, diving, floating or swimming and within 200 feet
4 of: (1) any beach frequented by persons who are bathing, wading, diving, floating
5 or swimming; (2) a swimming float, diving platform or lifeline; and (3) certain way
6 or landing floats. (NRS 488.600) Section 1 of this bill makes it a misdemeanor to
7 operate a vessel or permit a vessel to be operated at a speed in excess of 5 nautical
8 miles per hour within 600 feet of the shoreline of Lake Tahoe.
9 Under existing law, certain peace officers are authorized to take various actions
10 when a person violates certain sections of the Code of Ordinances of the Tahoe
11 Regional Planning Agency. (NRS 277.215) Section 2 of this bill replaces
12 references to ordinances no longer in effect with the current ordinances.
